=head1 DESCRIPTION

Additional configuration when you specify C<SPOT> as the
C<purchaseOption> for the C<CreateComputeNodeGroup> API action.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AllocationStrategy => Str

The Amazon EC2 allocation strategy Amazon Web Services PCS uses to
provision EC2 instances. Amazon Web Services PCS supports B<lowest
price>, B<capacity optimized>, and B<price capacity optimized>. For
more information, see Use allocation strategies to determine how EC2
Fleet or Spot Fleet fulfills Spot and On-Demand capacity
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/spot-fleet-allocation-strategy.html)
in the I<Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide>. If you don't provide
this option, it defaults to B<price capacity optimized>.



